@node not01 "AMIJOE REMARKS FROM MET@BOX"

@{B}AMIJOE @{UB}REMARKS FROM @{B}MET@BOX@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

What "stuns" me ....

We  are very glad to see that our recent announcement of the @{B}AmiJOE G3 @{UB}processor
upgrade  for  the @{B}AMIGA @{UB}contributes not only to the ongoing discussion about the
future  of  @{B}AMIGA@{UB},  but  also  to the design efforts of other companies. Even in
their  approach  towards  potential  customers  and users of such products these
people  have  started  to  think a little more customer-friendly. So, maybe it's
time to release some more educational stuff.

Our @{B}AmiJOE 1200 @{UB}is certainly meant for the majority of loyal Amigans still using
one of the most exciting sub-500-$ computers worldwide. But please note, that we
do  not provide the @{B}G3 @{UB}solution to owners of a customized @{B}A1200 @{UB}built into a big
tower  case.  Our  @{B}AmiJOE @{UB} will  fit into the regular keyboard-style case of the
original @{B}A 1200@{UB}. How do we do that? Engineering!

The @{B}AmiJOE 1200 @{UB}will have an expansion socket for a module also fitting into the
regular  @{B}A  1200@{UB},  offering  either  USB  or, without any difference in price, a
@{B}Fast-SCSII  2 @{UB} -  connector.  This module is part of the @{B}AmiJOE 1200 @{UB}product and
included in the price of 599 EURO.

@{B}AmiJOE  2000@{UB}/@{B}3000@{UB}/@{B}4000 @{UB} will obviously be a little bigger in size, so it has @{B}USB@{UB}
on  board. The @{B}PCI 2.1 @{UB}- compliant connector will be ready to connect to another
expansion  card, the @{B}MultiJOE@{UB}. At this stage, we don't want to disclose too much
information about the @{B}MultiJOE@{UB}, since others should think up their own ideas. We
are  only  going  to  let  you  know  that @{B}MultiJOE @{UB}will offer @{B}Ultra-SCSII @{UB}and a
complete  grafics  system,  which includes 2D/3D, video-in and digitizing, alpha
blending, genlock and flicker-reduction and AC-97-sound.

In  the  last  couple  of  months, we have learned a lot from our microprocessor
partners about @{B}G4 @{UB}and @{B}Altivec@{UB}. The major benefit of the @{B}G4 @{UB}(@{B}PPC 7400@{UB}) will be to
handle  up to 2 Mbyte of Backside Cache. It's some waste of time making 1 MB BSC
solutions  with  the @{B}G4@{UB}, so we will stick to the @{B}G3 @{UB}for now. One important thing
to understand is that this next generation of @{B}PowerPC @{UB}isn't ready to ship by the
time we will start to deliver the @{B}AmiJOE @{UB}to the market. As it becomes available,
there will be another product, too.

@{B}Firewire @{UB} maybe of interest for digital video editors, but it's our clear vision
that @{B}USB @{UB}will bring a broad range of modern peripherals into the @{B}Amiga @{UB}world. On
the  other  hand,  video  work  will  bring  much  fun and productivity with the
@{B}MultiJOE@{UB}, and this will be a turn-key- solution without paying a fortune.

EURO  pricing  is rather new, but makes it very easy for all customers in Europe
and  the  US  to  figure out their ticket into the @{B}G3 @{UB}sphere. We appreciate that
others  will  join  these  practices,  adding  also  more  transparency  to  the
competition.

As we still don't ask for prepayments, it's good to support people who need this
type  of  financials.  And  in  this case, it's very customer friendly to accept
orders  even  without  the  prepayment,  although  they  will have to pay a huge
interest charge on top.

Time will tell about reality.

Your's sincerely

@{I}Stefan Domeyer@{UI}
President & CEO
@{B}met@box AG@{UB}
