@node not02 "PHASE5 ANNOUNCES THE EXPANDIBILITY OF ITS G3/G4 ACCELERATORS FOR AMIGA"

@{B}PHASE5 @{UB}ANNOUNCES THE EXPANDIBILITY OF ITS @{B}G3/G4 @{UB}ACCELERATORS FOR @{B}AMIGA@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE@{UI}

@{B}phase  5  digital  products @{UB} is  excited  to  announce  that  the  next  step in
ground-breaking  technological  progress  will  take  place soon. Since we first
announced  the  @{B}Cyberstorm  G3/G4 @{UB} project  just  10  days ago, the overwhelming
response by the @{B}Amiga @{UB}Community has not only convinced us to extend the original
@{B}Cyberstorm  G3/G4 @{UB}project to an extended @{B}Amiga G3/G4 @{UB}product line. Driven by the
excitement  of  so  many  @{B}Amiga @{UB} users,  we  have spent many hours of additional
consideration  meanwhile,  discussing  the  requests  and  demands  by  the user
community,  and going into technical details and cost optimization. Today we can
present  some  exciting  news,  which  also  make  some of the statements of the
original  announcement  and the update obsolete already. However, if you had not
informed  yourself  about  this  development  before, please read these original
announcements  which  contain  information  about conditions and time frames for
this new product generation.

Following  the  history of world's most established processor upgrade technology
for  @{B}Amiga @{UB} computers, and implementing the experience of the innovator who made
the  @{B}PowerPC @{UB} technology for the @{B}Amiga @{UB}a reality, we at @{B}phase 5 digital products@{UB}
have  also  decided  to make this new technology available to a much larger user
base, and doing what we always did in the past years with our stunning products:
Offer  more value for less money! And that's what we will be doing again - so go
ahead and read about the new additional features at the new lower prices!

@{U}@{I}New models:@{UI}@{UU}

By  introducing  a  second product, the @{B}Blizzard G3/G4@{UB}, we will also provide the
stunning  @{B}G3/G4 @{UB} technology and performance to the users of @{B}A1200 Tower @{UB}systems.
Two models - one with @{B}G3 @{UB}and one with @{B}G4 @{UB}processors - can be ordered now. We are
also now taking orders for the 300MHz @{B}G4 @{UB}version of the @{B}Cyberstorm G3/G4@{UB}.

@{U}@{I}New features:@{UI}@{UU}

All  @{B}G3/G4 @{UB} boards  from  @{B}phase  5  digital  products @{UB} come with @{B}SCSI @{UB}on board -
@{B}UltraSCSI @{UB} on the @{B}A1200 @{UB}versions, @{B}UltraWide SCSI @{UB}on the @{B}A3000/A4000 @{UB}version. Our
proven  @{B}SCSI @{UB} technology,  which  has been providing unmatched performance since
seven  years,  will  provide  full  backwards  compatibility  with existing @{B}SCSI@{UB}
devices.  But  even  more  than that: With the integration of 400Mbit/s @{B}FireWire@{UB}
ports,  all  our  @{B}G3/G4 @{UB} boards  open the door to this future industry standard,
including the world of digital video devices

@{U}@{I}New prices:@{UI}@{UU}

By  proceeding with the related projections and calculations, and going into the
details,  we  have  been  able to determine new and improved pricings which will
make  these  stunning  products  even more attractive. Plus, we have changed the
pricing to EURO (for Europe) and US$ (for outside Europe).

@{U}@{I}New Order & Prepayment conditions:@{UI}@{UU}

In  order  to  proceed  quickly with the finalization and production of this new
product  line, we still require the originally announced quantity of back orders
with  a  prepayment  deposit.  All  customers  who  support our development will
receive  a  major  discount,  as  announced before (please see below for the new
prices  and discounts for the different models). But @{B}phase 5 digital products @{UB}is
also  ready  to  take  orders  now  without prepayment, for the suggested retail
prices  listed  for  the different products. These orders will not be shipped by
@{B}phase   5  digital  products @{UB} directly,  but  forwarded  to  local  dealers  and
distributors.

So far the overview of the major changes in the project. Now here comes the list
of  the  extended  and  updated  new @{B}G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}product line for the @{B}AMIGA @{UB}by @{B}phase 5
digital products@{UB}. Right now, users can choose out of the following four models:

@{B}BLIZZARD G3/300 @{UB}for @{B}A1200 Tower @{UB}systems
  * 300 MHz @{B}PowerPC750 @{UB}processor with 1MB fast Backside-Cache.
  * @{B}Ultra  SCSI @{UB} on  board  for  backwards  compatibility with a large number of
    existing @{B}SCSI @{UB}devices, providing a performance of up to 20MB/s.
  * Three  400MBit  @{B}FireWire @{UB}ports (@{B}IEEE-1394@{UB}), allowing the connection of up to
    63 devices, and opening the world of digital video to the @{B}AMIGA@{UB}
  * up to 1 GB SDRAM
  * @{B}PCI@{UB}-Bridge-Connector:   This   interface,   a   fully   @{B}PCI   2.1 @{UB} compliant
    implementation, allows the connection of @{B}PCI @{UB}devices or @{B}PCI @{UB}backplanes, thus
    allowing  the  expansion  of  the  @{B}Amiga @{UB}with all kinds of industry standard
    hardware products.
  * suggested  retail  price  of  EURO  669.00  (Europe)  or US$ 729.00 (outside
    Europe)
  * Customers  who  are  ready to pay a prepayment deposit of EURO 125 / US$ 140
