@node not06 "ANNOUNCE: SETDST 1.0"

ANNOUNCE: @{B}SETDST 1.0@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE@{UI}

Hi everyone!

Again  it's  the  time  of  the  year  birds start to collect bunches of nesting
material, the course of the sun reaches higher every day and trees begin to turn
green  again  ~~ in other words: spring break is here! Well, at least as long as
you're living in the northern hemisphere; for those living south of the equator:
have your warm clothes ready ;-)

Anyway,  it is very likely that your local time will change from or to "Daylight
Saving  Time  RSN"  or  it  even  has changed already recently and this is where
@{B}SetDST @{UB}comes in (at last :).

Its  main  task  is to adjust the @{B}Amiga @{UB}system time and the battery-backed clock
for Daylight Saving Time and standard time.

The  first  public  release,  @{B}SetDST  1.0@{UB},  has  been  uploaded to @{B}Aminet @{UB}and it
includes the following features (among others):
  * Can  be  run in the background as a commodity if you wish (for those who run
    their  @{B}Amiga @{UB} 24/7  and  usually don't have to reboot it for days, months or
    even years???).
  * Smoothely integrates into @{B}AmigaOS @{UB}by using current @{B}Locale @{UB}settings to select
    the correct timezone scheme as default behaviour.
  * Is  flexible  enough  to  be  used in various countries and other geographic
    regions.
  * Can use file notifications if you wish to update its behaviour on the fly.
  * Creates  and  manages up to 4 different environment variables to let various
    other  applications  make  use  of the current zone name, GMT offset and DST
    status.
  * It's freeware.

@{B}SetDST @{UB} can  be found in the 'util/time' directory at '@{B}de.aminet.net@{UB}' and should
be  available  on  all currently active @{B}Aminet @{UB}mirrors (hear that, @{B}wustl@{UB}? ;-) as
well.

Regards,

~~
