@node not23 "INTERVIEW WITH MR. PETRO TYSCHTSCHENKO"

INTERVIEW WITH MR. @{I}PETRO TYSCHTSCHENKO@{UI}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Date: 31 March 1999
Subject: Interview with Mr. @{I}Petro Tyschtschenko@{UI}
From: @{I}Christophe Heereman @{UI}alias @{I}Toffel@{UI}
Org: @{B}Waaslandia Amiga-Only Club @{UB}(@{B}WAC@{UB})

@{B}Waaslandia Amiga-Only Club @{UB}(@{B}WAC@{UB}), the biggest Belgian @{B}Amiga @{UB}user group, is proud
to present its latest interview... with Mr. @{I}Petro Tyschtschenko@{UI}.

This   interview   was   said   to   be  published  on  3  places  on  the  Net:
@{B}comp.sys.amiga.misc @{UB} and  very  soon also on @{B}titan.glo.be/~waasland @{UB}(the site of
@{B}WAC@{UB}) and @{B}come.to/amigbnl @{UB}(@{B}Amiga Benelux@{UB}). It will also appear in one of the next
club  mags  of  @{B}WAC @{UB} and perhaps in the new and only Dutch Amiga magazine "@{B}Amiga
Scene@{UB}".

The  "author"  is  @{I}Christophe  Heereman @{UI} alias  @{I}Toffel @{UI} and  can  be reached via
@{I}pheerema@xs4all.be @{UI} or  snail  mail/telephone  (see signature below). He and @{B}WAC@{UB}
thank Mr. @{I}Petro Tyschtschenko @{UI}for this interview.

@{U}@{I}QUESTIONS & ANSWERS@{UI}@{UU}

1)  Can you describe the new official structure of @{B}AMIGA@{UB}? Which departments have
been  installed  and  who  is  heading  what?  What  is  @{B}Amiga  Inc. @{UB} and  @{B}AMIGA
International, Inc. @{UB}within the current structure?
@{I}PTY @{UI} :  Of  course.  We  will  be  under  one  roof.  So  @{B}Amiga  Inc @{UB} and  @{B}AMIGA
International, Inc. @{UB}will be unified, which makes a lot of sense. @{B}Amiga @{UB}needs one
direction,  to  be  successful  in  the  future.  Due  to  legal  reason,  @{B}Amiga
International,  Inc. @{UB} will  be  still  a legal entity and I will be the Managing
Director.  I am reporting to Mr. @{I}Jim Collas@{UI}, the President and CEO of @{B}AMIGA@{UB}. @{I}Jim@{UI}
is  located in San Diego, Cal. and I will be remaining in Langen, Germany, close
to  Frankfurt  am  Main. As you can see on our webpage, we have already only one
website, independent if you click @{B}AMIGA.com @{UB}or @{B}AMIGA.de@{UB}.

2)  How  will  the  structure be expanded in the future? Will new departments be
installed? If so, which?
@{I}PTY@{UI}:  To  @{I}Jim  Collas @{UI}are reporting directly 6 Vicepresidents, including myself.
Dr.  @{I}Allan  Havemose@{UI},  he is located in San Jose, Cal. and he is responsible for
O/S  Software  Development  New Generation. We just have hired a System Engineer
for  Technical  Research  and  a  Controller,  responsible  for  all Finance and
Administration.  Both  will  be  located  in  San  Diego. @{I}Jeff Schindler @{UI}will be
responsible  for  Strategy  &  Product  Management  NG, and @{I}Jim van Holle@{UI}, is in
charge  for  Marketing  NG.  Both  are also located in San Diego. As I mentioned
already,  I  will  stay in Langen and will be responsible for the existing @{B}AMIGA@{UB}
Line  (sorry  but I do not like the expression CLASSIC) and will take care about
the  contingency  of  this  great  Technology,  for  licensing  of  the existing
Technology  and  Merchandise Products, for Sales and Distribution worldwide, for
Usergroup  Communication and Support, for the @{B}AMIGA @{UB}Website and for Logistic and
Service.  The plan is to hire in the states minimum 50 people in addition to the
management,  mainly  for  research  and development. You should be aware that an
organisation  is  always a living organism and have to be flexible to the market
needs.  I  think  with  the  existing  Management we have a real strong force to
conquer together the future and to be very succesful as a team.

3)  Are  there  plans  to  install  country departments for other countries than
Germany  and the USA? If so, when will we see @{B}AMIGA UK@{UB}, @{B}AMIGA Belgium@{UB}, @{B}AMIGA The
Netherlands@{UB},...?
@{I}PTY @{UI} :  As  I explained the organisation has to be flexible, and I am quite sure
that  there will be a lot of changes in the near future. If the market is asking
after subsidiaries, please be sure we will install those. I will take care about
this.

4)  Which continents/countries/regions form the main target for @{B}AMIGA @{UB}concerning
the @{B}Amiga-II@{UB}?
@{I}PTY @{UI} :  We  are  an  international  company.  And  we  will  target our products
worldwide.  The  world  gets  smaller  and smaller and we have to acting global.
@{B}AMIGA @{UB}always operated worldwide, we will not change this.

5)  Will  we  see  sport  teams  wearing  @{B}Amiga @{UB} shirts again? Will we see @{B}Amiga@{UB}
commercials  on TV, in papers, in computer magazines,... Can you tell us already
some marketing/publicity/PR plans?
@{I}PTY @{UI} :  We  have  a  big  goal  and  to  reach  this  target we have to act in a
professional  way. We will work out a Marketing Plan for the NG and we will soon
present our new strategy.

6)  Are there plans to contact schools, universities, study centra,... to inform
them of the @{B}Amiga-II@{UB}? Will 'special offers' be provided?
@{I}PTY @{UI} :  Also  that  is a very important move, we will perform. But please do not
forget,  after  two  years  slow motion, unfortuneately, we are just starting to
generate  a  lot of activities driven by @{I}Jim Collas@{UI}. The transition time will be
always critical, but I have no worry we must be successful on the end.

7)  What does @{B}AMIGA @{UB}mean with "in the tradition of the @{B}AMIGA 500@{UB}" when they talk
about  the  low-end  @{B}Amiga-II@{UB}?  The  tradition of quality, revolution, quantity,
sight,...?
@{I}PTY @{UI} :  @{B}AMIGA @{UB}always have had a low end and a high end product. We will continue
this  strategy.  But please watch our new announcements which you can see on our
website  soon.  Our  goal  is  to  create a revolutionary and compelling systems
architecture  and  operating  environment  for  multimedia computers and digital
information  appliances  which  can  easily  be imbedded into consumer computing
devices and enables innovative Internet services.

8)  The  Developer  @{B}Amiga @{UB} will  be  produced by @{B}AMIGA@{UB}. What about the hand-held
Internet  device  and  the  low-end  @{B}Amiga-II@{UB}? Will this be released by @{B}AMIGA @{UB}or
@{B}Gateway, Inc.@{UB}?
@{I}PTY @{UI} :  In  the  current  stage  we are talking with a lot of possible strategic
partners and we will also give soon an answer to this question.

9)  Does  @{B}AMIGA @{UB} plan  to  release  other  products  after  these? Will we see a
tower-based  @{B}Amiga-II @{UB} for  the  people  who  need  a  lot of cards and internal
peripherals?
@{I}PTY @{UI}  :  Please  believe  me  we  are  working  on  a  lot  of  very  intresting
subjects.....but  it  is  to early to talk about this today... Please understand
this.
10) What is true about the rumour that @{B}Sony @{UB}and @{B}Amiga @{UB}are working together? Will
the @{B}PSX2@{UB}, as some people say, be that first @{B}Amiga-II @{UB}game console?
@{I}PTY @{UI} : Rumours, rumours, rumours. Of course, as I mentioned before we have had a
lot  of very intresting discussions with different possible partners, but we are
still in the process of evaluation.

11)  On  @{B}amiga.org @{UB} and different other sites/forums we could read that @{B}Corel @{UB}is
planning  to develop for the @{B}Amiga-II@{UB}. Can you confirm/deny this? What about the
rumours  that  @{B}Adobe @{UB}will join the market too? Are there already other strategic
partners for the moment (except for @{B}QSSL@{UB}) and if so, when will we know them?
@{I}PTY @{UI} :  Here  I  have  to  give  the  same  answer....We  have had a lot of very
intresting  discussions  with very potential companies. But it is toooo early to
talk about this.....

12)  How  do  you  see  the  future  of the @{B}Amiga@{UB}? What is the minimum amount of
@{B}Amiga-II@{UB}s  that  should  be  sold in the first 12 months after the release in 2Q
2000? What does @{B}AMIGA @{UB}expect?
@{I}PTY @{UI} : As you know I never gave up in my live. I always believe in @{B}AMIGA@{UB}, even a
lot  of  people laughed about me. I went through two bankruptcies and never lost
my  faith  in  @{B}AMIGA@{UB}......We  will have a bright future.....the time is ripe for
success....

13)  What  is  your  personal  opinion  about the future? How big do you see the
market in short, middle long, long and very long term? What will be the place of
the @{B}Amiga @{UB}in the computer world?
@{I}PTY @{UI}: I do not have a cristal ball to answer you this question, but what I heard
so  far,  the  vision,  and  what  I have seen sofar, the professionality of @{I}Jim
Collas@{UI},  we will soon have the first success with our @{B}OS 3.5@{UB}, followed by the NG
in November 99. We will be in Cologne in November 99 showing suprises and we are
planning  to  be  in  Las  Vegas at the @{B}Comdex @{UB}this year as well.....We are also
planning to have a @{B}World of Amiga @{UB}in London.

14)  When  @{B}AMIGA @{UB}will be as big (or bigger) than @{B}M$@{UB}, what will @{B}AMIGA @{UB}do when the
court tells you to split the company? :))
@{I}PTY @{UI} :  We  are  not  trying to be a monopoly....we will be a joice...but a good
one....maybe the best. I think we will never have this problem.

(The latest question is a question from one of our club members :))

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

