@node not44 "THE INTERNET & OS 3.5"

THE INTERNET & @{B}OS 3.5@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Here  are some more details regarding @{B}OS 3.5 @{UB}as revealed by @{B}Haage&Partner @{UB}at the
@{B}AUGS@{UB}-Meeting.

@{I}Internet@{UI}:

  * A  special  version of @{B}AWeb @{UB}will be the Browser and the TCP/IP-stack will be
    @{B}Miami@{UB}.   Integrated   Network-support.   The   E-Mail-API   and  the  simple
    E-Mail-Client will be from the author of @{B}Voodoo @{UB}and @{B}New York@{UB}.

@{I}@{B}Workbench@{UB}@{UI}:

  * It  wouldn't be necessary anymore to use the Shift-Key when moving more than
    one  icon.  An  "Unselect"  will  be  possible  when  more  than one icon is
    selected.  All  Preferences-Programs  will get the new @{B}Reaction@{UB}-surface. The
    Submenus of the @{B}WB @{UB}will be optimized for a better handling.

@{I}Icon Library@{UI}:

  * When  selecting,  the  icons will start to "glow" when dragging them they'll
    get  semi-transparent.  Via the "Info"Option it will now also be possible to
    set  the  process-priority.  The current and the @{B}NewIcons @{UB}will be supported.
    The @{B}AppIcons @{UB}will now be able to be animated.

@{I}Reaction@{UI}:

  * The   Tool   @{B}Reactor @{UB}  will   enable   software-authors   to   use  the  new
    @{B}Reaction@{UB}-surface  with their own software. One of the highlights of @{B}Reaction@{UB}
    is  the  possibility to have a color-gradient in the background of a window.
    Also bugs in the "asl.library" will be removed.

@{I}PowerPC@{UI}:

  * @{B}WarpUp @{UB} will be integrated in it's latest version. An important part will be
    the Preferences-settings which will complement the integration.

@{I}Installer@{UI}:

  * The  installer  will  be able to be opened on an own screen. This screen can
    have  a  color-gradient.  New  will  be the possibility to go steps backward
    during installation.

@{I}Printers@{UI}:

  * The  printer-support  will be redesigned completely, so that 24-bit-printing
    will  be  possible  on  the @{B}WB@{UB}. @{B}CyberGraphX @{UB}and @{B}Picasso96 @{UB}will be supported.
    There will be only one Printer-Setting in the future, which will also have a
    preview-window showing immediately the changed settings.

@{I}Datatypes@{UI}:

  * Reworked  and improved, now also 24-bit-capable. New are datatypes for @{B}AIFF@{UB},
    @{B}JPG @{UB}and @{B}GIF@{UB}. Complete rework of the @{B}Amigaguide-Datatype@{UB}.

The  documentation will be in HTML in German and English (and hopefully in other
languages  like  Spanish, French, Italian, Swedish, etc.). Release date is still
August.  First Beta-Tests will start in 3 weeks. @{B}AmigaOS 3.5 @{UB}wil be delivered on
CD-ROM for 99,50 DM.
