@node not49 "WORLD OF AMIGA '99 - IT'S GOING AHEAD!"

@{B}WORLD OF AMIGA '99 @{UB}- IT'S GOING AHEAD!
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

@{B}PBA Events @{UB}in association with @{B}AmigaSoc UK @{UB}are pleased to announce that the most
eagerly awaited @{B}Amiga @{UB}event on everyone's calendar is going ahead. The show will
be on the weekend of 24th and 25th July.

Many  people  have expressed the need to host the UK's premier @{B}Amiga @{UB}event at an
alternative venue. Although the Novotel was selected for reasons of tradition in
the  past,  the  time has come to break with tradition and go for something new.
This  year,  we'll  be holding the event in a prestigious Kensington venue which
we're sure you'll agree is a huge improvement over the Novotel!

In addition to the usual things people have come to expect from the show, we are
aiming  to run a number of other events within the show. These will be organised
with  the  help  of  UK user groups, so you can guarantee that the place will be
brimming with @{B}Amiga @{UB}experts with brains just waiting to be picked!
  * Games  competitions:  @{B}Amiga @{UB} multi-player  games  are getting better all the
    time.  Now's  your chance to play them with loads of other people... and you
    might even win a prize!
  * An  @{B}Amiga @{UB} cybercafe: If you're not on the Internet already, see how easy it
    is to get your @{B}Amiga @{UB}connected!
  * Seminars:  Following  on  from  last  year's  hugely  successful  series  of
    seminars,  we'll  be  getting  leading @{B}Amiga @{UB}people to make presentations on
    various  subjects (if you'd like to hold a seminar, get in touch with @{I}Andrew
    Elia @{UI}at @{I}andrew@uk.amigasoc.org @{UI}now).
  * How-to  sessions:  If  you're  in  any  doubt as to the best way to go about
    towering  your  @{B}A1200@{UB}, or getting on the Internet, @{B}Amiga @{UB}experts from around
    the  UK  will show you how (if you've got any ideas for potential workshops,
    then  contact  @{I}Andrew  Elia @{UI} at the above adress or use the forms soon to be
    available on our website).
  * Shareware  registration:  Your  chance  to  register  some top quality @{B}Amiga@{UB}
    software without all the hassle of sending money to far off places.
  * A  user  group  hospitality  area: Those that are members of registered user
    groups  can  relax  in  a  private and informal atmosphere while getting the
    chance to hobnob with @{B}Amiga @{UB}celebrities from around the world.
  * Stands for user groups: If you're not a member of a user group, then you can
    come  along  and  meet representatives from your nearest group. On the other
    hand,  if  you're  a  user  group  and you'd like to take the opportunity to
    recruit  some more members, then the @{B}WOA @{UB}show is the perfect place to start.
    If  your  user  group wants a piece of the action, E-Mail @{I}Chris Livermore @{UI}at
    @{I}chrisl@uk.amigasoc.org@{UI}.
  * The inimitable @{B}Annex@{UB}: Get autographs and kisses from @{B}Amiga@{UB}'s own pop group!

Undoubtedly,  one  of the most exciting things happening at the show will be the
launch  of  @{B}OS  3.5@{UB}. All being well, this product should be launched at the show
and  will  be  on  sale.  You  won't  get  another chance to try before you buy!
Additionally,  the  next  generation  @{B}Amiga@{UB}s  are just around the corner, so you
never know what else you might see!

The  @{B}1998  AAA  awards @{UB} will also be presented at the show, so you can see first
hand who will be collecting this year's international award as well as the first
ever @{B}UK AAA @{UB}award.

The official @{B}World Of Amiga @{UB}website is already on-line. All the latest news will
be  posted  here.  We are currently in the process of updating it to include all
the  information  visitors to the show could possibly need, including details of
hotels,  a  map  of  the  venue,  our  growing  list of exhibitors, and any news
relating  to  the  show  as it becomes available to us. We also hope to offer an
on-line  ticket  ordering  system  courtesy of @{B}IMM Studios@{UB}. If there's something
else  you  feel  we  should  provide  through the site then drop us an E-Mail at
@{I}andrew@uk.amigasoc.org@{UI}!

Be in no doubt, this show has got the full backing of @{B}Amiga@{UB}.

Tickets  will  be priced at £7.50 for adults, and £5.00 for under 14s. This year
we will also be offering special rates for families. Two adults and two children
(under  14) enter for only £15.00! Additionally, for people wishing to attend on
both  days of the show, there will be a special booth on Saturday that will sell
tickets to existing ticket holders for Sunday's show for a mere £2.00 (£1.00 for
under 14s). There will also be a number of tempting door prizes. Details will be
made available on @{B}www.worldofamiga.com@{UB}.

As  far as exhibitors are concerned, we are aiming to provide a competitive rate
this   year,   and   will   also   be   offering   special  low-cost  tables  to
companies/organisations  who  are on a tight budget. In short, we want to please
everyone!

You won't want to miss it!
